Sec. 13.026. CORD. (a) A cord is equal to 128 cubic feet or
the contents of a space 8 feet long, 4 feet wide, and 4 feet high.
(b) A cord of wood intended for use as fuel is the amount of
wood contained in a space of 128 cubic feet when the wood is ranked
and well-stowed and one-half the kerf of the wood is included.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1024, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

